	(502,'ErrorPage','2007-10-01 12:47:25','2012-08-29 10:03:38','page-not-found','Page not found',NULL,'<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Sorry, it seems you were trying to access a page that doesn\'t exist.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Please check the spelling of the URL you were trying to access and try again.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,0,7,NULL,0,0,'Published',NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers',1,1,0,15,1,NULL,NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers','en_US',0,0,0),
	(6676,'Page','2012-05-25 10:09:09','2013-10-21 12:47:01','easy-page-editing','Easy page editing',NULL,'<p class=\"intro\">It\'s easy to locate a page to edit, and the rich-text editor makes content updating very simple. Adding pages, links, images and videos can all be done from your web browser without technical or HTML knowledge.</p>\n<h3>Beautiful interface</h3>\n<p>The first thing you will notice is an entirely refreshed content management user interface. Developers will appreciate it is built on HTML5 and jQuery, but content authors will just love that they can do their work more quickly, using a beautiful user interface. </p>\n<p>A site can have any number of page <em>types</em>, each with their own editable fields, templates and behaviour. A developer can invent new types of fields and behaviour both in the CMS and for the public-facing website. This enables both the CMS and the website to be perfectly tailored to suit requirements.</p>\n<p>The notion of a Draft and Published site enables you to save and preview your changes before the public see it.</p>\n<p><img class=\"leftAlone\" title=\"\" src=\"assets/Uploads/_resampled/resizedimage750552-Screen-Shot-2012-05-25-at-10.23.44-AM.png\" alt=\"Screen Shot of SS3 Interface\" width=\"750\" height=\"552\"></p>','New Features',NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,0,1,NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers',0,0,6686,24,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',NULL,0,0,0),
	(4302,'Page','2007-11-20 12:56:41','2013-10-21 11:57:55','drag-and-drop-sitetree','Drag & drop sitetree',NULL,'<h2 style=\"text-align: left;\">The pages and files that make up the site tree of a SilverStripe website can be reshuffled by dragging and dropping them around.</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">This makes re-arranging your site a fun and fast activity<em>. </em>SilverStripe CMS lets you structure the website in a logical, organised way by \"nesting\" pages in a hierarchy.</p>\n<p>As you alter the site tree shown below, menus and lists throughout the website are updated. Clicking on a page in the site tree lets you edit that page.</p>\n<p><img class=\"left\" title=\"\" src=\"assets/Uploads/_resampled/resizedimage600359-screenshot-sitetree.png\" alt=\"screenshot sitetree\" height=\"359\" width=\"600\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><em><img class=\"left\" title=\"\" src=\"assets/Uploads/screenshot-dragdropsitemap.png\" alt=\"screenshot dragdrop sitemap\" height=\"298\" width=\"256\"></em></p>\n<p><em> </em></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>','Drag & drop',NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,0,7,NULL,1,0,'Published',NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers',1,1,6686,43,0.9,NULL,NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers','en_US',0,0,0),
	(6670,'ErrorPage','2010-08-19 12:31:00','2012-05-21 19:34:28','server-error','Server error',NULL,'<p>Sorry, there was a problem with handling your request.</p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,0,8,NULL,0,0,'New page',NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers',0,0,0,2,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit','en_US',0,0,0),
	(6672,'Page','2012-05-24 17:32:21','2013-10-21 16:33:22','media-insertion','Media insertion',NULL,'<p>You can insert media from a variety of sites into your page, thanks to the magic of oEmbed! Just click the \"insert media\" button (it looks like a picture of a tree) and enter the URL of your video (YouTube, Vimeo), photo (Flickr, or URL) or presentation (SlideShare).</p>\n<p><img class=\"leftAlone\" title=\"\" src=\"assets/Uploads/_resampled/resizedimage600327-media-inserter.png\" alt=\"media inserter demo\"></p>\n<p>Example embedded of video:</p>\n<div class=\"captionImage leftAlone\" style=\"width: 600px;\">[embed width=\"600\" height=\"337\" class=\"center\" thumbnail=\"http://b.vimeocdn.com/ts/103/759/103759717_640.jpg?r\"]http://vimeo.com/16842606[/embed]\n<p class=\"caption\">You can also embed SlideShare presentations.</p>\n<p class=\"caption\">[embed width=\"425\" height=\"355\" class=\"left\" thumbnail=\"http://www.slideshare.net/silverstripe/silverstripe-participates-in-gsoc-2012?r\"]http://www.slideshare.net/silverstripe/silverstripe-participates-in-gsoc-2012[/embed]</p>\n</div>','Media insertion',NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,0,3,NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers',0,0,6686,19,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',NULL,0,0,0),
	(6678,'Page','2012-05-25 10:58:19','2016-02-15 14:03:26','theme','Simple Theme','Theme','<p class=\"intro\">Simple theme is the default theme which comes bundled with a new installation of SilverStripe. If you download SilverStripe without this theme you can also find it on <a title=\"Simple theme download\" href=\"https://github.com/silverstripe-themes/silverstripe-simple\" target=\"_blank\">github.com</a> to use and alter as you wish.</p>\n<p>This theme has been kindly donated by <a title=\"More information about Sara (Innovatif)\" href=\"http://www.saratusar.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Sara (Innovatif)</a> as part of the SilverStripe theme competition in 2012. Themes can be tailored to the needs of a business or individual through basic HTML and CSS which every web developer is familiar with. Within a theme developers have the opportunity to build custom features like forms, image carousels and news pages using SilverStripe CMS and Framework speed up the development process.</p>\n<p>Themes usually consist of built-in typographical styles so that content authors can choose from a predefined set font choices with set colours and size. Removing the option for content authors to chose font colours and faces produces better professionalism of the website, and makes the editing interface simpler. It also means you can later change the visual apperance or theme of your website without altering your written content.</p>\n<p>The Simple theme is used within the tutorials on <a title=\"SilverStripe documentation\" href=\"http://docs.silverstripe.org\">docs.silverstripe.org</a>. Providing developers with real examples of how themes can be customized and altered to each specific need. You are welcome to customize and reuse this theme for your own personal or business use.</p>','Styles',NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,0,5,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers',0,0,0,21,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',NULL,0,0,0),
	(7202,'Page','2013-10-08 12:35:21','2013-10-21 12:29:15','file-management','File management',NULL,'<p>With the SilverStripe CMS, users have the capability to upload images and files like PDFs and Word documents to be able to share publicly to the viewer of the site. Uploading an image is easy - just drag the file you want into the insert image window from your desktop as pictured below. CMS editors also have the option to add files to their content areas from other places on the web.</p>\n<p><img class=\"left\" title=\"\" src=\"assets/Uploads/_resampled/resizedimage600424-Screen-Shot-2012-05-25-at-10.41.34-AM2.png\" alt=\"Drag drop image demo\" width=\"600\" height=\"424\"></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,0,2,NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers',0,0,6686,6,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',NULL,0,0,0),
	(6681,'Page','2012-05-25 13:52:37','2013-10-21 12:33:58','security-and-audit-trail','Security & Audit Trail',NULL,'<p>Every save made to a page contributes to an audit trail. You can compare old versions with each other and roll back to them in the History tab.</p>\n<p>A powerful security system allows viewing and editing of pages to be restricted to various users. Users and groups can be created and this can all provide the basis for secure login areas or more elaborate publishing workflow.</p>\n<p><img class=\"leftAlone\" title=\"\" src=\"assets/Uploads/_resampled/resizedimage600421-silverstripe-security-page.png\" alt=\"silverstripe security page\" width=\"600\" height=\"421\"></p>','Security & Audit Trail',NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,0,9,NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers',0,0,6686,12,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Anyone','OnlyTheseUsers',NULL,0,0,0),
	(6682,'Page','2012-06-28 13:00:19','2013-10-21 12:31:35','listview','Listview',NULL,'<p>ListView makes finding and updating pages on very large sites considerably easier. In the CMS while browsing the familiar site tree, click the Treeview icon. Now you can work with the site tree using filters and paginated lists.</p>\n<p><img class=\"left\" title=\"\" src=\"assets/Uploads/_resampled/resizedimage699514-listview-509rows-screenshot.png\" alt=\"listview 509rows screenshot\" width=\"699\" height=\"514\"></p>','Treeview',NULL,NULL,0,1,NULL,0,4,NULL,1,0,NULL,NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers',0,0,6686,13,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',NULL,0,0,0),
	(6686,'Page','2012-06-29 08:46:36','2016-02-15 14:01:40','features','SilverStripe CMS & Framework features','Features','<p class=\"intro\"><span>The SilverStripe CMS is easy for both developers and content authors to work with. The SilverStripe </span>Framework<span> keeps the code tucked away neatly so that it can be accessed easily by programmers without getting in the way of content authors. </span></p>\n<p><span>An out-of-the-box installation of the SilverStripe CMS provides all the day-to-day editing control you are likely to need as a content author. With WYSIWYG and drag &amp; drop functions, site editors have full control over the way they want their content to look without needing to know HTML. If you can use a word processor, you can use the SilverStripe CMS. Images and files can be added through a drag &amp; drop interface, and pages and templates are fully customisable. Themes and widgets allow even more extensions. Developers can further customise the interface to suit how you work as an author and as a business.</span></p>\n<p><a title=\"SilverStripe Software\" href=\"http://www.silverstripe.org/software/\">For a complete list of features please visit silverstripe.org</a></p>',NULL,NULL,NULL,1,1,NULL,0,3,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,'Anyone','LoggedInUsers',0,0,0,24,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Inherit','Inherit',NULL,0,0,0),
